HEADWORD: Sequoiene
<hw>Se*quoi"ene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A hydrocarbon (<chform>C13H10</chform>) obtained in white
fluorescent crystals, in the distillation products of the needles of the
California ⟦ldquo⟧big tree⟦rdquo⟧ (<spn>Sequoia
gigantea</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

